PRIMITIVE VALUE
  var a = 3;
  var b = a;

  BY VALUE (all primitive types)
  * b will be given a copy of a's value, it is located
    in a new address dedicated to the value of b.


OBJECT VALUE
  var a = {};
  var b = a;

  BY REFERENCE ( all objects, including functions)
  * b just points to the location of the object reference
    b a
  * no new object is created
